race.comment: LITTLE JEANIE (9) is an honest commodity who has hit the top-five in seven of her past eight starts and doesn't know how to run a bad race. Has placed two of three over this track and trip and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Should be right there when the whips are cracking. SCUD (2) was a dominant Port Macquarie winner last time out and will be ready to peak now third-up from the spell. Can make it back-to-back. FREELAND (4) has won three of her past four and it's hard to knock mares in form. Include in calculations. IMPOSANT (1) best of the rest with the 3kg claim from the low draw.
